<dl id="n10068f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10068f">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10068f"> 68(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">D</font>&apos;s cask <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n10068f"><li>FW 452.24 </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/lexqA.htm#n10068f">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/l39qA.htm#n10068f">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n10068f">MS BL 47482b-31</ms> </li><li>JJA 57:063 <a name="qA2d" href="../../ff/fdra/qda.htm#qA2d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/q/qA2d.htm#n10068f">Draft: III&sect;2A.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Jules C&eacute;sar dit que les Gaulois, d&apos;une province &agrave; l&apos;autre, s&apos;avertissaient de tous les mouvements de son arm&eacute;e, au moyen de feux allum&eacute;s sur le sommet des montagnes. On trouve encore en France les ruines de tours d&apos;observation b&acirc;ties par les Romains, &agrave; Arles; Uz&egrave;s, &agrave; Bellegarde, ainsi que la tour Magne &agrave; N&icirc;mes; ce sont autant de vestiges de la t&eacute;l&eacute;graphie a&eacute;rienne des Romains. Ces tours &eacute;taient command&eacute;es par des officiers sp&eacute;ciaux, que l&apos;on voit repr&eacute;sent&eacute;s, <mark>le casque</mark> en t&ecirc;te et <font color="green">[303]</font> l&apos;&eacute;p&eacute;e en main, dans l&apos;un des compartiments les plus &eacute;lev&eacute;s de la colonne Trajane, &eacute;rig&eacute;e &agrave; Rome en l&apos;honneur de l&apos;empereur Trajan en 112. <font color="green">[Julius Caesar said the Gauls, from one province to the other, warned each other of the movements of his army, by means of signal fires at the tops of the mountains. One still finds in France the ruins of observation towers built by the Romans, in Arles, Uz&egrave;s, in Bellegarde, just as the Magne tower in N&icirc;mes; these are all witnesses of the old Roman telegraph system. These towers were under the command of special officers, which are represented, with their helmets on their head and their sword in hand, in one of the compartments of Trajan&apos;s column, erected in Rome in honour of the emperor Trajan in 112]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 303-4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
